               <head/>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85100085">
                  <summary>1 copy of Dīvān-i Jāmī by ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_47-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="358v"/>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20688">Dīvān-i Jāmī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20688">دیوان جامی</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_90042997">عبد الرحمن جامی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم *** هست صلاح بر خوان کریم </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">چه خوش با در کاشانه غم *** دو همدم درد دل گویند باهم</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>This manuscript includes both parts of Jāmī's first dīvān. </p>
                        <p>The ghazals begin on f60r; the muqaṭṭaʿāt begin on f294r; the rubāʿiyyāt begin on f297v. </p>
                        <p>On f1r, there are five seals. Only one of these remains at all legible, that of (Ṣ?)amnat Khān, dated 1130AH (1717-8). </p>
                        <p>On f0r, Jones notes that the manuscript was a gift from Francis Gladwin on the 5th November 1783. </p>
                     </note>
                     <decoNote>There is a blue and gold headpiece on f1v that is designed to evoke the Kaʿbah.</decoNote>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
